  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Developing Young Environmental Champions in Ghana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Solid waste management is a major problem in Ghana. The exponential growth in population and changes in consumer patterns have resulted in incessant littering and indiscriminate dumping in public spaces that have dire consequences on the environment, wildlife and public health.  We will create ECO- CLUBS in various schools to engage kids and teachers in waste management techniques such as reducing, reusing, recycling and composting. We will also undertake greening and beautification activities.</narrative>
  </description>
